We can simplify the fraction $\frac{16}{20}$ by dividing both the numerator and denominator by their greatest common factor, which is 4. 




\begin{align*}
\frac{16}{20} &= \frac{16 \div 4}{20 \div 4} \\
&= \frac{4}{5}
\end{align*}




Therefore, $\frac{16}{20}$ simplifies to $\frac{4}{5}$.

